[{"classname": "aeroplane", "wiki": "A powered heavier-than-air aircraft with fixed wings."}, {"classname": "bicycle", "wiki": "A vehicle that has two wheels, one behind the other, a steering handle, and a saddle seat or seats and is usually propelled by the action of a rider’s feet upon pedals."}, {"classname": "bird", "wiki": "A member of the class of animals Aves in the phylum Chordata, characterized by being warm-blooded, having feathers and wings usually capable of flight, having a beaked mouth, and laying eggs."}, {"classname": "boat", "wiki": "A craft used for transportation of goods, fishing, racing, recreational cruising, or military use on or in the water, propelled by oars or outboard motor or inboard motor or by wind."}, {"classname": "bottle", "wiki": "A container, typically made of glass or plastic and having a tapered neck, used primarily for holding liquids."}, {"classname": "bus", "wiki": "A motor vehicle for transporting large numbers of people along roads."}, {"classname": "car", "wiki": "A wheeled vehicle that moves independently, with at least three wheels, powered mechanically, steered by a driver and mostly for personal transportation."}, {"classname": "cat", "wiki": "An animal of the family Felidae:
 Synonym: felid"}, {"classname": "chair", "wiki": "An item of furniture used to sit on or in, comprising a seat, legs or wheels, back, and sometimes arm rests, for use by one person. Compare stool, couch, sofa, settee, loveseat and bench."}, {"classname": "cow", "wiki": "An adult female of the species Bos taurus, especially one that has calved."}, {"classname": "diningtable", "wiki": null}, {"classname": "dog", "wiki": "A mammal, Canis familiaris or Canis lupus familiaris, that has been domesticated for thousands of years, of highly variable appearance due to human breeding."}, {"classname": "horse", "wiki": "Any of several animals related to Equus ferus caballus."}, {"classname": "motorbike", "wiki": "A motorcycle."}, {"classname": "person", "wiki": "An individual; usually a human being. [from 13th c.]

Each person is unique, both mentally and physically."}, {"classname": "pottedplant", "wiki": null}, {"classname": "sheep", "wiki": "A woolly ruminant of the genus Ovis."}, {"classname": "sofa", "wiki": "A raised area of a building's floor, usually covered with carpeting, used for sitting."}, {"classname": "train", "wiki": "Elongated portion."}, {"classname": "tvmonitor", "wiki": null}]
